  sodium: 4.3 g
  serving size: 676
time required: 20 minutes
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C.

Heat a glug of @?olive oil{for frying} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @chicken breast{260%g}(diced) and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry, turning frequently until the chicken is browned on the outside, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging.

While the chicken is cooking, halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%tin} in a #colander{}, put half of them into a #bowl{} and roughly mash with a #potato masher{}.

Add the remaining whole beans to the bowl.

Drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}.

Once the chicken is browned, add the shallot to the pan.

Fry, stirring frequently until the shallot has softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @Mexican style spice mix{2%tbsp}, sweetcorn and half the garlic. Cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

> TIP: Add less spice if you don't like heat.

Pour in the @tomato passata{1%jar}, @water{200%ml}, @chicken stock paste{15%g} and black beans (whole and mashed).

Season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and @sugar{1/4%tsp}.

Bring to the boil, stirring continuously, then reduce the heat to medium.

Cover the pan with a #lid{} or some #foil{} and simmer until the mixture is thick and the chicken is cooked, ~{6-8%minutes}. Stir every 2 mins or so.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, in a small bowl, mix together the remaining garlic, and @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}(for garlic bread).

While the stew cooks, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}(grated).

Cut each @ciabatta{2} in half.

Place on a #baking tray{}, spread the garlic oil on the cut side and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bake until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the stew is cooked, stir in the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time until wilted.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if needed.

Remove the pan from the heat, taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Serve in #bowls{} with the cheese scattered on top and the garlic ciabatta alongside. Enjoy!

> Step 1 MOD: If you've opted to get diced chicken breast instead of thigh, cook in the same way.